1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:02,299
(Previously) I just wanted
your scent to extract perfume.

2
00:00:02,300 --> 00:00:02,800
Huh?
Gaysorn!

3
00:00:03,501 --> 00:00:06,799
You said once you find your mother,
you'll go back home.

4
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,200
Then how am I supposed to live?

5
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:12,500
The Mudan people will
never abandon their partners.

6
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:14,200
And what if my mother is actually dead?

7
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:17,400
Even if there's no one left,
I will always stay by your side.

8
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:20,400
I've decided not to produce
the Mudan perfume anymore.

9
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:21,500
Damn it!

10
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:23,700
See you soon.

11
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:24,800
Okay.

12
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,200
Gaysorn?

13
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:39,800
Gaysorn!

14
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:11,280
[June 4, 2010]

15
00:01:11,376 --> 00:01:13,400
[Dear Bussaba, ]

16
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:16,560
[I was in a car accident
and I really want to see you.]

17
00:01:16,561 --> 00:01:19,120
[Please come to Bangkok
as fast as possible.]

18
00:01:19,140 --> 00:01:21,641
[The person who gave you the letter]

19
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:24,680
[will help you get to the city.]

20
00:01:26,281 --> 00:01:31,282
[I love and miss you, Pruek]

21
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:53,600
"Flower Boy"
(Episode 6)

22
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:09,356
Why are you home so early?

23
00:03:20,756 --> 00:03:21,757
Oh! It's you.

24
00:03:23,116 --> 00:03:24,876
If you're here to see
Scent, he is not here.

25
00:03:25,012 --> 00:03:27,116
No, we're not. We're here to see you.

26
00:03:27,594 --> 00:03:29,194
We have something important to tell you.

27
00:03:32,553 --> 00:03:34,233
Don't worry about Scent, he wouldn't mind.

28
00:03:34,336 --> 00:03:35,656
I used to come here all the time.

29
00:03:36,063 --> 00:03:37,064
Hey!

30
00:03:37,290 --> 00:03:38,291
Hey!

31
00:03:44,788 --> 00:03:46,628
If you have something
to tell me, just say it.

32
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:50,981
Do you know that.

33
00:03:52,092 --> 00:03:54,276
Scent wanted to make a
perfume out of your scent?

34
00:04:06,271 --> 00:04:08,436
What is the new perfume
that Scent talked about?

35
00:04:09,236 --> 00:04:10,396
Why hasn't it done yet?

36
00:04:12,914 --> 00:04:14,554
Why didn't you say anything? Just say it.

37
00:04:17,308 --> 00:04:19,196
If I tell you this, you
can't let anyone know

38
00:04:19,714 --> 00:04:20,903
or I will be fired for sure.

39
00:04:22,652 --> 00:04:23,653
Sure.

40
00:04:24,076 --> 00:04:25,077
Tell us.

41
00:04:28,798 --> 00:04:30,327
It is Gaysorn's scent.

42
00:04:31,836 --> 00:04:33,276
So you fooled him?

43
00:04:33,756 --> 00:04:34,876
Well…yeah.

44
00:04:35,382 --> 00:04:36,422
But…

45
00:04:36,447 --> 00:04:38,223
he wanted to come to
Bangkok all by himself.

46
00:04:38,618 --> 00:04:40,276
Scent didn't push him or force him to.

47
00:04:42,236 --> 00:04:43,736
Still, you fooled him.

48
00:04:45,330 --> 00:04:46,490
What do you expect him to do?

49
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:48,836
Do you want Scent to tell Gaysorn that

50
00:04:49,036 --> 00:04:51,296
he wanted Gaysorn's
scent to make a perfume?

51
00:04:51,594 --> 00:04:52,595
Who would agree to that?

52
00:04:53,377 --> 00:04:56,436
Scent acted so nice and kind to Gaysorn,

53
00:04:56,906 --> 00:04:58,516
because he wanted something from him?

54
00:04:58,999 --> 00:05:00,996
If we can produce perfume out of Gaysorn,

55
00:05:01,716 --> 00:05:02,876
we think Kusuma will make it.

56
00:05:03,302 --> 00:05:04,382
Poor Gaysorn.

57
00:05:05,196 --> 00:05:06,716
He must have thought that.

58
00:05:07,036 --> 00:05:08,436
Scent really loved him.

59
00:05:08,770 --> 00:05:11,036
Instead, Scent manipulated
him to believe that.

60
00:05:14,042 --> 00:05:15,196
Scent didn't tell you

61
00:05:15,216 --> 00:05:17,336
that he would make a perfume
from your scent, did he?

62
00:05:17,856 --> 00:05:20,196
I don't think so. That's so creepy.

63
00:05:21,156 --> 00:05:22,157
Stop saying that.

64
00:05:23,036 --> 00:05:24,836
If he understood it,
he would be so hurt.

65
00:05:27,356 --> 00:05:29,236
So Scent didn't tell you the truth, did he?

66
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:32,020
That he would make a
perfume from your scent?

67
00:05:35,991 --> 00:05:36,992
You know it well,

68
00:05:37,286 --> 00:05:39,236
about how crazy I am over your scent.

69
00:05:40,456 --> 00:05:42,236
I want to preserve your scent

70
00:05:43,076 --> 00:05:44,077
and that's it.

71
00:05:47,231 --> 00:05:49,156
He never told me about selling it

72
00:05:51,796 --> 00:05:53,876
he said that he'd make a perfume
because he loved me.

73
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:36,896
Gaysorn?

74
00:06:51,802 --> 00:06:52,803
Gaysorn!

75
00:07:04,431 --> 00:07:05,916
I'll prepare a bed for you.

76
00:07:08,260 --> 00:07:09,261
No need to.

77
00:07:11,555 --> 00:07:12,556
I can sleep here.

78
00:07:14,158 --> 00:07:15,596
I won't trouble you for so long.

79
00:07:16,831 --> 00:07:19,516
You can stay here as long as you want.

80
00:07:21,658 --> 00:07:23,156
It's been a rough day for you,

81
00:07:24,143 --> 00:07:25,196
you should rest.

82
00:07:26,626 --> 00:07:28,156
We can talk about it tomorrow.

83
00:08:17,551 --> 00:08:19,031
Do you want to go to Bangkok with me?

84
00:08:19,196 --> 00:08:20,596
If you want to search for your mom,

85
00:08:21,316 --> 00:08:22,317
I can help you with that?

86
00:08:23,146 --> 00:08:24,147
You can?

87
00:08:24,815 --> 00:08:25,816
Absolutely.

88
00:08:31,383 --> 00:08:32,823
Come on, let me wipe it off for you.

89
00:08:35,495 --> 00:08:37,586
Where is the cloth to wipe my sweat?

90
00:08:38,676 --> 00:08:41,316
Don't worry about it,
you can use a new one.

91
00:08:41,727 --> 00:08:42,728
I have plenty of them.

92
00:08:48,466 --> 00:08:49,636
I am as curious as he is.

93
00:08:49,932 --> 00:08:52,436
Why did you ask a courier from Kusuma

94
00:08:52,796 --> 00:08:54,916
to come and collect Gaysorn's cloth
with his sweat?

95
00:08:56,642 --> 00:08:59,178
What are you trying to do?

96
00:09:02,796 --> 00:09:05,236
I won't let anything hurt you again,

97
00:09:06,956 --> 00:09:07,957
please trust me.

98
00:09:10,436 --> 00:09:11,437
I trust you.

99
00:09:32,103 --> 00:09:34,236
You lied to me so I
would trust you completely.

100
00:09:36,887 --> 00:09:37,996
That is what you do.

101
00:10:20,522 --> 00:10:21,796
Where are you, Gaysorn?

102
00:11:00,836 --> 00:11:01,837
Did you eat anything?

103
00:11:34,471 --> 00:11:35,472
You should eat something.

104
00:12:05,783 --> 00:12:06,796
Any updates?

105
00:12:09,714 --> 00:12:10,715
None.

106
00:12:11,846 --> 00:12:13,482
There are no clothes left in the closet

107
00:12:15,316 --> 00:12:16,756
which means that he wanted to leave.

108
00:12:17,674 --> 00:12:18,794
You think he'd go back home?

109
00:12:18,964 --> 00:12:20,462
What did you do to upset him?

110
00:12:23,196 --> 00:12:24,236
I have no idea.

111
00:12:25,695 --> 00:12:27,036
We planned a date last night.

112
00:12:28,236 --> 00:12:29,796
He said that he had something for me.

113
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:33,836
He seemed so happy yesterday.

114
00:12:35,736 --> 00:12:37,216
I think something must have happened.

115
00:12:37,959 --> 00:12:39,639
That's why he left without saying goodbye.

116
00:12:49,012 --> 00:12:50,898
I will ask to see footage
from surveillance cameras

117
00:12:50,922 --> 00:12:52,322
maybe I could see him when he left.

118
00:12:52,364 --> 00:12:53,796
Scent! Scent!

119
00:12:54,178 --> 00:12:55,179
What?

120
00:12:55,836 --> 00:12:56,837
Why don't you

121
00:12:57,308 --> 00:12:59,396
try to call Ray or Mekin?

122
00:13:02,068 --> 00:13:03,069
Ray?

123
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:04,200
Mekin?

124
00:13:04,703 --> 00:13:05,704
Why?

125
00:13:06,367 --> 00:13:08,436
Gaysorn left without saying a word

126
00:13:08,458 --> 00:13:09,916
and I can only think of one thing.

127
00:13:11,156 --> 00:13:13,076
Sun! What is it?

128
00:13:13,336 --> 00:13:14,337
Calm down.

129
00:13:14,436 --> 00:13:15,916
- What is it?
- Please calm down.

130
00:13:16,735 --> 00:13:18,596
I accidentally did something so stupid.

131
00:13:35,665 --> 00:13:37,462
Hey, you should drink it.

132
00:13:37,786 --> 00:13:39,386
We can find something to eat on the way.

133
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:41,917
Thank you.

134
00:14:08,290 --> 00:14:09,291
Should we get going?

135
00:14:10,356 --> 00:14:11,397
Sure, let's go.

136
00:14:28,716 --> 00:14:29,876
Did you bring Gaysorn here?

137
00:14:30,276 --> 00:14:31,476
He asked me to bring him here.

138
00:14:31,863 --> 00:14:32,956
Let me talk to him.

139
00:14:33,164 --> 00:14:34,964
- He doesn't want to…
- None of your business.

140
00:14:35,127 --> 00:14:36,207
I don't want to be involved

141
00:14:36,903 --> 00:14:38,396
but I feel really bad for him.

142
00:14:38,634 --> 00:14:40,596
He was fooled and he knew nothing about it.

143
00:14:42,858 --> 00:14:43,859
Move.

144
00:14:49,503 --> 00:14:50,504
I'm sorry.

145
00:14:51,828 --> 00:14:53,487
Please let me explain everything.

146
00:14:53,972 --> 00:14:54,996
I know all about it

147
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:57,673
you don't need to explain.

148
00:14:58,636 --> 00:15:00,136
Wait, wait.

149
00:15:04,476 --> 00:15:05,477
I'm sorry.

150
00:15:06,503 --> 00:15:07,756
I'm sorry for deceiving you.

151
00:15:09,536 --> 00:15:10,537
It's more than once.

152
00:15:12,223 --> 00:15:13,596
You've deceived me so many times,

153
00:15:16,196 --> 00:15:17,276
you did it over and over.

154
00:15:19,543 --> 00:15:20,996
Have you ever told me the truth?

155
00:15:29,106 --> 00:15:30,236
That was the beginning.

156
00:15:30,922 --> 00:15:32,956
But I called off all the projects.

157
00:15:35,962 --> 00:15:37,036
And I promise you

158
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:39,996
that I won't use your scent again.

159
00:15:44,930 --> 00:15:46,156
What do you think of me?

160
00:15:48,503 --> 00:15:49,636
A guinea pig?

161
00:15:52,138 --> 00:15:53,676
Have you ever seen me as a human?

162
00:15:59,156 --> 00:16:01,436
- Please listen to me.
- I don't trust your words anymore.

163
00:16:21,396 --> 00:16:22,516
Don't follow me.

164
00:18:10,532 --> 00:18:11,996
You need to clear your head

165
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:14,078
and everything will be fine.

166
00:18:17,007 --> 00:18:18,008
Thank you.

167
00:18:21,769 --> 00:18:24,596
Do you have any plans after this?

168
00:18:30,324 --> 00:18:31,586
I've thought about it

169
00:18:33,999 --> 00:18:35,596
and I decided not to go back to Scent.

170
00:18:38,623 --> 00:18:39,636
I'm going home.

171
00:18:42,756 --> 00:18:43,757
Home?

172
00:18:44,636 --> 00:18:45,637
You mean?

173
00:18:47,874 --> 00:18:48,994
I'm going back to mountains.

174
00:18:52,044 --> 00:18:54,836
I told Mata that
I would be looking for Mom for a month.

175
00:18:55,471 --> 00:18:56,956
Now it's been more than a month.

176
00:18:57,844 --> 00:18:59,396
I haven't seen my mom so I should go.

177
00:19:00,228 --> 00:19:01,428
Don't lose hope just yet.

178
00:19:02,511 --> 00:19:04,716
I can help you find your mom.

179
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:07,316
I mean it's your mom.

180
00:19:08,236 --> 00:19:10,536
You can't just give up easily, right?

181
00:19:14,804 --> 00:19:15,916
We can help you.

182
00:19:32,706 --> 00:19:35,116
This is my mom. Her name is Bussaba.

183
00:19:39,494 --> 00:19:41,596
She met my dad more than 20 years ago

184
00:19:42,284 --> 00:19:43,796
and she followed him to Bangkok.

185
00:19:45,876 --> 00:19:46,916
My dad

186
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:49,476
was a perfumer for Kusuma Company.

187
00:19:54,263 --> 00:19:55,388
When she was pregnant,

188
00:19:56,098 --> 00:19:58,063
Dad wanted to extract a
perfume with her scent.

189
00:20:00,386 --> 00:20:02,516
Mudan people are that fragrant?

190
00:20:07,943 --> 00:20:09,136
Our scent

191
00:20:09,580 --> 00:20:10,836
will remind people

192
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:12,636
of their happiness.

193
00:20:14,039 --> 00:20:15,040
How so?

194
00:20:27,732 --> 00:20:29,116
Ray, honey?

195
00:20:30,452 --> 00:20:32,596
You need to drink up, honey.

196
00:20:36,812 --> 00:20:37,813
Smell of something soft,

197
00:20:40,151 --> 00:20:41,196
like warm milk.

198
00:20:41,287 --> 00:20:42,488
Ray,

199
00:20:42,791 --> 00:20:45,236
do you want some of this? It will be sweet.

200
00:20:45,831 --> 00:20:47,916
- Sure, Mommy.
- Come on.

201
00:20:49,718 --> 00:20:50,796
You need to drink it now.

202
00:20:52,546 --> 00:20:53,547
Honey.

203
00:20:56,522 --> 00:20:58,576
- So many of them.
- Sure, darling.

204
00:20:58,580 --> 00:21:00,036
Smells so great.

205
00:21:00,223 --> 00:21:01,596
- Smells nice, right?
- Here.

206
00:21:02,698 --> 00:21:04,076
It's hot, let me feed you.

207
00:21:15,476 --> 00:21:16,577
Roses.

208
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:19,917
Vanilla.

209
00:21:25,378 --> 00:21:26,379
I get it now.

210
00:21:28,076 --> 00:21:29,756
It really makes me feel something.

211
00:21:35,756 --> 00:21:37,676
But your scent is really light.

212
00:21:39,535 --> 00:21:41,615
I don't think it is strong
enough to make a perfume.

213
00:21:42,858 --> 00:21:44,716
Normal people can't even smell me.

214
00:21:45,818 --> 00:21:47,956
The outsiders can only smell Mudan people

215
00:21:48,738 --> 00:21:49,836
when we want them to.

216
00:21:51,479 --> 00:21:52,836
But it will be very light.

217
00:21:55,388 --> 00:21:56,389
Unless,

218
00:22:01,204 --> 00:22:02,916
when we are in love.

219
00:22:05,036 --> 00:22:06,396
That's when the scent is stronger.

220
00:22:12,954 --> 00:22:15,364
I see it now.

221
00:22:15,407 --> 00:22:17,743
Scent was trying to please
you because he wanted

222
00:22:18,452 --> 00:22:20,076
you to give him sweet scent.

223
00:22:36,276 --> 00:22:37,956
Just put them there, thank you.

224
00:22:48,956 --> 00:22:50,736
So many papers, what are you looking for?

225
00:22:50,962 --> 00:22:52,736
News, reports

226
00:22:53,244 --> 00:22:55,996
and all documents related to
Pruek and Busaba perfume.

227
00:22:57,623 --> 00:22:59,956
What for? To make up with Gaysorn?

228
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:03,920
Like I have a chance to make up to him,

229
00:23:04,770 --> 00:23:06,396
he won't believe me anymore.

230
00:23:12,058 --> 00:23:13,178
What is the reason for this?

231
00:23:18,956 --> 00:23:20,636
I want to do it for him.

232
00:23:23,548 --> 00:23:24,837
I really love him.

233
00:23:31,762 --> 00:23:33,436
Fine, I will help you.

234
00:24:09,036 --> 00:24:11,436
Mata said that Mom gave
birth to me on the mountain.

235
00:24:12,969 --> 00:24:14,369
Dad told her to wait for him there.

236
00:24:15,292 --> 00:24:17,092
One day, she went to
the city to look for him

237
00:24:17,666 --> 00:24:18,786
and she has never come back.

238
00:24:21,010 --> 00:24:23,536
So…what about your dad?

239
00:24:25,362 --> 00:24:28,756
Uncle Wittaya said that he fell of
the stairs and died a long time ago.

240
00:24:29,802 --> 00:24:31,677
But nobody knows where my mom is.

241
00:24:34,746 --> 00:24:35,747
I see.

242
00:24:37,863 --> 00:24:40,636
That's why Busaba perfume was launched
for one time only.

243
00:24:42,356 --> 00:24:44,396
Your parents were missing.

244
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:48,736
Are you sure about this?

245
00:24:49,836 --> 00:24:51,396
Cognoscenti knows about this.

246
00:24:52,876 --> 00:24:54,396
My mom had one bottle of this.

247
00:25:01,716 --> 00:25:02,996
Mom? Did you send it to me?

248
00:25:03,324 --> 00:25:04,596
I sent it to you, dear.

249
00:25:04,995 --> 00:25:06,455
I got it now, thanks.

250
00:25:08,356 --> 00:25:10,516
This is Busaba perfume.

251
00:25:11,356 --> 00:25:12,956
My mom sent me the picture.

252
00:25:15,007 --> 00:25:16,436
Busaba Perfume?

253
00:25:16,956 --> 00:25:19,556
That's right, it was so famous

254
00:25:20,007 --> 00:25:21,556
20 years go.

255
00:25:21,676 --> 00:25:25,156
They said that the perfumer passed away

256
00:25:25,716 --> 00:25:28,436
so the company couldn't
produce more of this product.

257
00:25:28,461 --> 00:25:30,285
She kept one as a memento.

258
00:25:31,274 --> 00:25:32,316
20 years?

259
00:25:34,244 --> 00:25:35,245
20 years? Really?

260
00:25:36,644 --> 00:25:37,836
What is wrong with that?

261
00:25:39,852 --> 00:25:41,036
Mom, I gotta go.

262
00:25:41,692 --> 00:25:42,693
Okay.

263
00:25:43,722 --> 00:25:45,636
When Mom came to Bangkok to look for Dad.

264
00:25:46,354 --> 00:25:47,476
I was four years old.

265
00:25:48,476 --> 00:25:49,477
I am now 20 years old.

266
00:25:50,596 --> 00:25:51,597
It means that.

267
00:25:52,159 --> 00:25:54,236
Mom went to see Dad 16 years ago.

268
00:25:57,226 --> 00:25:58,227
And?

269
00:25:58,836 --> 00:26:00,396
I heard that.

270
00:26:00,506 --> 00:26:03,036
Busaba's perfumer died 20 years go.

271
00:26:04,810 --> 00:26:05,916
Does it mean that

272
00:26:07,774 --> 00:26:09,678
my dad was dead for four years

273
00:26:10,796 --> 00:26:12,116
before Mom went to see him?

274
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:16,076
If this is how the story went,

275
00:26:16,578 --> 00:26:17,738
who did your mom come here to see?

276
00:26:26,356 --> 00:26:28,076
When did my dad die?

277
00:27:38,146 --> 00:27:39,147
From now on,

278
00:27:40,116 --> 00:27:41,956
you are my whole world.

279
00:27:46,567 --> 00:27:48,276
You are my whole world, too.

280
00:27:52,516 --> 00:27:53,876
You've deceived me so many times,

281
00:27:54,996 --> 00:27:56,116
you did it over and over.

282
00:27:58,308 --> 00:27:59,756
Have you ever told me the truth?

283
00:28:01,116 --> 00:28:02,396
What do you think of me?

284
00:28:04,658 --> 00:28:05,836
A guinea pig?

285
00:28:08,396 --> 00:28:09,837
Have you ever seen me as a human?

286
00:28:15,436 --> 00:28:17,716
- Please listen to me.
- I don't trust your words anymore.

287
00:28:23,703 --> 00:28:24,704
Don't follow me.

288
00:29:27,436 --> 00:29:28,437
Gaysorn.

289
00:29:29,872 --> 00:29:31,196
Please don't be like this.

290
00:29:33,183 --> 00:29:35,356
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

291
00:29:45,476 --> 00:29:47,196
I'm a horrible person, I'm so bad.

292
00:29:47,775 --> 00:29:48,976
You don't have to forgive me

293
00:29:52,316 --> 00:29:54,436
but there is one thing that
I have never lied to you about,

294
00:29:55,676 --> 00:29:56,677
I love you.

295
00:29:57,019 --> 00:29:58,956
Our love is real, Gaysorn.

296
00:30:00,082 --> 00:30:02,076
I love you and you love me.

297
00:30:02,540 --> 00:30:03,541
No,

298
00:30:04,836 --> 00:30:05,956
that was before it happened.

299
00:30:08,235 --> 00:30:09,876
I don't love you anymore.

300
00:30:12,847 --> 00:30:14,136
My heart doesn't beat fast

301
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:18,276
and I have no scent for you anymore.

302
00:30:27,479 --> 00:30:28,481
I'm here

303
00:30:30,572 --> 00:30:32,136
to talk about me.

304
00:30:52,199 --> 00:30:53,316
I want to know

305
00:30:55,724 --> 00:30:57,436
when my dad died exactly.

306
00:32:01,418 --> 00:32:02,419
Gaysorn, let's go.

307
00:34:35,535 --> 00:34:36,636
Morning.

308
00:34:41,407 --> 00:34:42,408
What's that?

309
00:34:42,670 --> 00:34:45,516
Some papers that I got
from Scent yesterday.

310
00:34:46,816 --> 00:34:48,522
It can tell when my dad died.

311
00:34:50,269 --> 00:34:52,509
It said that the employment contract ended

312
00:34:52,534 --> 00:34:56,094
on October 18th, 2006.
The cause was an accident.

313
00:34:57,658 --> 00:34:58,659
It was

314
00:34:59,503 --> 00:35:00,596
exactly 20 years ago.

315
00:35:04,047 --> 00:35:06,076
When my mom went to the city,

316
00:35:08,292 --> 00:35:09,556
Dad was already dead.

317
00:35:11,010 --> 00:35:13,796
Who did she visit?

318
00:35:15,706 --> 00:35:17,236
Your mom lived in the mountains,

319
00:35:18,796 --> 00:35:20,556
who told her to come to the city?

320
00:35:22,786 --> 00:35:23,956
Mata told me that.

321
00:35:24,578 --> 00:35:26,876
Mom got a letter saying
that Dad was severely injured

322
00:35:27,676 --> 00:35:29,796
and she needed to go to
the city as fast as possible.

323
00:35:30,677 --> 00:35:32,756
If your dad wasn't there,

324
00:35:33,324 --> 00:35:34,524
then someone lied to your mom.

325
00:35:37,154 --> 00:35:38,692
I think we need to
take a look at the letter

326
00:35:38,716 --> 00:35:40,186
to see where it was sent from.

327
00:35:41,511 --> 00:35:43,116
Do you have it with you?

328
00:35:51,810 --> 00:35:52,811
Mata.

329
00:36:13,081 --> 00:36:14,082
You can send me off here.

330
00:36:15,225 --> 00:36:16,665
I think I should accompany you back.

331
00:36:17,002 --> 00:36:18,003
I don't think so.

332
00:36:18,175 --> 00:36:20,836
Mudan people are not familiar
with outsiders coming to our village.

333
00:36:23,884 --> 00:36:26,756
Fine, I'll be waiting in the city.

334
00:36:27,121 --> 00:36:29,436
This is a mobile phone.

335
00:36:29,783 --> 00:36:31,191
My number is already stored in here.

336
00:36:31,215 --> 00:36:32,735
When you're done, just give me a call.

337
00:36:36,817 --> 00:36:37,818
Thank you.

338
00:36:46,143 --> 00:36:47,144
Gaysorn!

339
00:36:48,796 --> 00:36:49,797
Gaysorn!

340
00:36:52,735 --> 00:36:53,736
Tawan.

341
00:36:59,876 --> 00:37:00,956
You're back, aren't you?

342
00:37:03,316 --> 00:37:04,356
You're safe, right?

343
00:37:11,788 --> 00:37:12,789
Where are you off to?

344
00:37:12,930 --> 00:37:15,316
How could you ask me that?
We're here to look for you.

345
00:37:16,021 --> 00:37:17,916
We were so worried about you.

346
00:37:25,292 --> 00:37:26,293
Who is this?

347
00:37:27,116 --> 00:37:28,117
He is not that guy.

348
00:37:31,271 --> 00:37:32,272
This is Mekin.

349
00:37:33,324 --> 00:37:34,325
He just sent me off.

350
00:37:37,644 --> 00:37:38,714
I'm fine right here, you can go.

351
00:37:38,738 --> 00:37:40,226
I'm with Mata and Tawan

352
00:37:40,855 --> 00:37:41,856
so don't worry about me.

353
00:37:44,161 --> 00:37:45,162
Okay.

354
00:37:57,236 --> 00:37:58,237
Mata.

355
00:38:28,473 --> 00:38:29,474
Mata.

356
00:38:30,788 --> 00:38:31,789
Mata.

357
00:38:32,847 --> 00:38:34,436
I'm sorry that I ran off.

358
00:38:41,815 --> 00:38:44,396
You need to apologize to the whole village

359
00:38:45,691 --> 00:38:48,916
for burning down their houses.

360
00:38:50,143 --> 00:38:52,196
Every house caught fire.

361
00:38:54,572 --> 00:38:55,573
Here.

362
00:38:56,857 --> 00:38:58,255
Apologize to him,

363
00:38:58,906 --> 00:39:01,196
to him and to everyone.

364
00:39:06,623 --> 00:39:08,476
You're the successor.

365
00:39:09,018 --> 00:39:10,676
How could you do that?

366
00:39:14,394 --> 00:39:15,716
I'm sorry everyone.

367
00:39:17,767 --> 00:39:18,996
I'm really sorry.

368
00:39:20,407 --> 00:39:21,656
I didn't mean to.

369
00:39:22,460 --> 00:39:24,106
I didn't know it would be like that.

370
00:39:25,804 --> 00:39:26,805
I'm so sorry.

371
00:39:28,679 --> 00:39:29,680
Where's the guy?

372
00:39:31,136 --> 00:39:32,256
Why wasn't he here with you?

373
00:39:47,567 --> 00:39:50,156
You're not going to get Gaysorn back?

374
00:39:52,767 --> 00:39:53,996
There is no use.

375
00:39:54,772 --> 00:39:56,036
He is not scented anymore.

376
00:39:56,713 --> 00:39:57,714
Let him go.

377
00:39:57,959 --> 00:40:00,276
What? What about your dad?

378
00:40:00,471 --> 00:40:01,756
What about our company?

379
00:40:07,196 --> 00:40:09,636
- Anurak!
- Dad!

380
00:40:09,761 --> 00:40:10,762
Dad!

381
00:40:11,581 --> 00:40:12,582
What's wrong?

382
00:40:13,804 --> 00:40:14,805
What's going on?

383
00:40:17,239 --> 00:40:18,240
Bro!

384
00:40:19,396 --> 00:40:20,836
Please wait outside.

385
00:40:21,004 --> 00:40:22,796
Please go.

386
00:40:22,948 --> 00:40:23,996
- Hey!
- Come here.

387
00:40:24,591 --> 00:40:25,592
Come here with me.

388
00:40:26,334 --> 00:40:28,356
- What's going on?
- We need to talk outside.

389
00:40:32,129 --> 00:40:34,167
- What is it?
- Stop complaining already.

390
00:40:34,497 --> 00:40:35,498
You know it well

391
00:40:35,559 --> 00:40:37,876
that nothing can compare to the Mudan scent.

392
00:40:38,892 --> 00:40:40,596
If you still care about the family,

393
00:40:41,244 --> 00:40:42,506
you need to get the kid back.

394
00:40:42,682 --> 00:40:43,683
I already told you.

395
00:40:44,170 --> 00:40:46,556
- We are over.
- No!

396
00:40:48,575 --> 00:40:49,836
You need to tell him

397
00:40:50,319 --> 00:40:52,320
if he wants to know where his mom is,

398
00:40:52,556 --> 00:40:53,876
then he needs to follow you back.

399
00:41:11,839 --> 00:41:13,479
I didn't know it would turn out this way.

400
00:41:15,607 --> 00:41:17,636
I heard that if he can smell my scent,

401
00:41:18,087 --> 00:41:19,436
then he is my soulmate.

402
00:41:21,180 --> 00:41:23,876
Why did my soulmate hurt me like this?

403
00:41:32,732 --> 00:41:34,716
City people must be

404
00:41:35,316 --> 00:41:37,796
different from us, they're
not like us, I guess.

405
00:41:41,444 --> 00:41:42,445
What about you?

406
00:41:43,391 --> 00:41:44,392
You're here.

407
00:41:45,112 --> 00:41:46,476
Are you back for good?

408
00:41:50,644 --> 00:41:51,716
Or you need something?

409
00:41:55,151 --> 00:41:56,152
Mata,

410
00:41:56,969 --> 00:41:59,418
do you remember
about the letter that Mom received?

411
00:42:01,423 --> 00:42:02,996
It said that she needed to see Dad.

412
00:42:04,138 --> 00:42:05,139
I do remember.

413
00:42:06,447 --> 00:42:08,276
I told you everything about the letter.

414
00:42:09,263 --> 00:42:11,556
Do you remember what it said?

415
00:42:11,850 --> 00:42:13,086
Who sent it to her?

416
00:42:19,172 --> 00:42:20,292
Here, just read it yourself.

417
00:42:28,986 --> 00:42:32,676
June 4, 2010.

418
00:42:33,596 --> 00:42:34,836
Dear Bussaba,

419
00:42:35,636 --> 00:42:36,876
I was in a car accident and.

420
00:42:38,042 --> 00:42:39,636
I really want to see you.

421
00:42:40,372 --> 00:42:42,436
Please come to Bangkok as fast as possible.

422
00:42:43,396 --> 00:42:45,196
The person who gave you the letter

423
00:42:45,796 --> 00:42:47,796
will help you get to the city.

424
00:42:48,212 --> 00:42:50,986
I love and miss you, Pruek.

425
00:42:53,836 --> 00:42:54,837
What is it?

426
00:42:55,907 --> 00:42:58,796
My dad fell off the stairs.
He wasn't in a car accident.

427
00:43:00,330 --> 00:43:02,036
You mean that this was a fake letter?

428
00:43:05,335 --> 00:43:07,796
June 2010.

429
00:43:09,527 --> 00:43:12,076
He died in 2006.

430
00:43:14,098 --> 00:43:17,476
You mean that the sender of this letter

431
00:43:18,594 --> 00:43:20,836
tricked Bussaba to go to the city?

432
00:43:23,876 --> 00:43:24,877
Who did that?

433
00:43:53,164 --> 00:43:54,165
Scent,

434
00:43:54,275 --> 00:43:55,356
I got some snack for you.

435
00:43:57,543 --> 00:43:58,716
Where did you get them?

436
00:43:59,788 --> 00:44:01,516
That lady gave them to me.

437
00:44:02,151 --> 00:44:03,152
Here.

438
00:44:04,500 --> 00:44:06,200
(Free distribution.
(Not for sale.)

439
00:44:06,746 --> 00:44:08,136
People here are so nice.

440
00:44:10,747 --> 00:44:11,748
Hey!

441
00:44:12,436 --> 00:44:15,196
You shouldn't accept
anything from a stranger.

442
00:44:16,783 --> 00:44:17,784
Why's that?

443
00:44:23,351 --> 00:44:26,196
Sometimes people do good things
because they want something back.

444
00:44:28,193 --> 00:44:29,194
What about you?

445
00:44:30,212 --> 00:44:31,276
You are so nice to me.

446
00:44:32,332 --> 00:44:33,333
What do you want?

447
00:44:35,180 --> 00:44:36,181
Me?

448
00:44:39,831 --> 00:44:40,876
I want…

449
00:44:47,871 --> 00:44:48,996
I want you.

450
00:45:03,431 --> 00:45:04,743
Nobody sees us here.

451
00:45:05,706 --> 00:45:06,707
Eat it.

452
00:45:10,218 --> 00:45:11,219
Is it good?

453
00:45:13,625 --> 00:45:14,756
You're chewing so hard.

454
00:45:18,292 --> 00:45:19,396
It must be really good.

455
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:33,640
(Next Episode) This is the letter
that someone sent to your mother.

456
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:36,800
I'll investigate this for you.
You can trust me, Gaysorn.

457
00:45:37,200 --> 00:45:39,900
Scent, do you want to put
your own father in prison?

458
00:45:40,300 --> 00:45:42,500
Dad, can you please tell me?

459
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:45,000
What am I supposed to do, Dad?

460
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:51,799
We want to bring the person
who harmed my mother to justice.

461
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:53,976
There's barely any evidence left to
help us convict the culprit.

462
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,476
The person who wrote that letter to
trick Brother Sorn's mother is the culprit.

463
00:45:56,500 --> 00:45:58,000
The Kusuma people.

464
00:45:59,200 --> 00:46:00,400
Gaysorn...

465
00:46:00,500 --> 00:46:01,700
I miss you.
